.TH "drm_dp_link_choose" 9 "drm_dp_link_choose" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_link_choose \- choose the lowest possible configuration for a mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dp_link_choose
.BI "(struct drm_dp_link *link "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
DRM DP link object
.IP "mode" 12
DRM display mode
.IP "info" 12
DRM display information
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
According to the eDP specification, a source should select a configuration
with the lowest number of lanes and the lowest possible link rate that can
match the bitrate requirements of a video mode. However it must ensure not
to exceed the capabilities of the sink.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
